			<li class="cd-faq-title"><h2>Privacy</h2></li>
			<li>
				<a class="cd-faq-trigger" href="#0">Can I specify my own private encryption key?</a>
				<div class="cd-faq-content">
					<p>Yes, if you're a registered user you can chooce your key by typing it.</p>
				</div> <!-- cd-faq-content -->
			</li>

			<li>
				<a class="cd-faq-trigger" href="#0">I forgot my encryption key! Can I get it back?</a>
				<div class="cd-faq-content">
					<p>No, and if you don't remember it your messages (that have been encrypted with those key) are lost forever, Kalypso can't do anything because she doesn't store anything except your username and your email.</p>
				</div> <!-- cd-faq-content -->
			</li>

			<li>
				<a class="cd-faq-trigger" href="#0">Can I access my account data?</a>
				<div class="cd-faq-content">
					<p>Kalypso encrypts your messages without saving them on her servers. She does not even store the encrypted results!</br>
				So, your data stored in Kalypso's servers are: your username, your e-mail and your crypted recovery answer. Anything else: no password, no caches, no messages, no encryption keys.</p>
				</div> <!-- cd-faq-content -->
			</li>
